Diagnosis. Male imago.
1) sternum IX with truncated posterior margin, medial line blackish (
Fig. 3D
); 2) pedestal of each side touching basally, inner projection digitiform, apically rounded, outer projection slender, long and apically rounded (
Figs 3D and 3G
); 3) main lobe of penis with basal half expanded laterally (ear-like) and with transverse ridge (
Figs 3D–I
); 4) dorsal surface of penis rugose (
Fig. 3F
); 5) secondary lobe translucent, slender and cylindrical, almost reaching the apex of main lobe (
Figs 3E–I
). 
Female imago.
1) anteromedian socket oval to circular in shape, internal sclerites with two openings (
Figs 4D–F
).
